<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 13 at 10:31PM CDT  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern
Somervell, Hamilton, southeastern Erath, Coryell, central Lampasas,
Bosque, west central Hill and southeastern Mills Counties through
1130 PM CDT...
At 1030 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Iredell to 15 miles southwest of Evant.
Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Copperas Cove, Gatesville, Clifton, Hamilton, Meridian, Hico, Evant,
Iredell, Cranfills Gap, Meridian State Park, Fort Gates, Lometa,
Walnut Springs, Morgan and South Mountain.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
